idml.longDescription:
• READY MADE - Your package will include 2 panels printed blackout curtains with 2 matched solid tiebacks, each panels measures 42x95 inch with 6 nice grommets, the inner diamater is 1.6" of each, easy to install and slid, suitable for standard curtain rods.
  • MATERIAL - Deconovo Thermal curtains are made with 100% high-precision polyester fabric with triple weave technology. The middle layer of black yarn makes them have a good blackout effect (the darker the color the better the effect). And the thick fabric gives it a good drape.
  • MUTI FUNCTION CURTAIN - Use Deconovo room darkening curtains to create a dark and quiet environment, bring you a good TV watching experience, protect furniture exposed to the sun while also helping you save on heating and cooling costs in your home. The biggest benefit is that it gives you a good sleep, free from the disturbance of strong daylight.
  • NICE DECORATION - The eye-catching Sliver wave line and dots pattern are printed on the front of the curtain, add a fresh look to your interior and is perfect for decorating children's rooms, nursery, bedrooms, dorm rooms, apartments, offices, living rooms and dining rooms.
  • WASH TIP - In order to keep the curtains durable, it is recommended to wash by hand, clean below 86°F and iron low temperature. Do not bleach, do not tumble dry.

customerReviews.reviewText:
I got the Grayish White color with gold constellation print. The color is a slightly blue toned light gray. It's not darker than expected. The blue bend is a slight undertone, which I couldn't necessarily see when I opened the package, but put next to my neutral tone light gray walls I can see that the curtains are more cool. The gold print is more noticeable than I expected. It's a bright gold. I hand washed the curtains, but might just try machine washing them to see if this print fades. 

They hand washed well. The fabric has a very nice feel to it regardless of price. Thick cotton-type, not polyester feel. The back of the curtain is the same color as the front, minus the print. It doesn't have the black backing like blackout curtains do. I do need to hem it a bit as there wasn't a perfect size for my window, so I might just end up turning the print side to the window.

The curtains are room darkening, but not blackout. It's enough for the sun not to wake me up, to keep the window area from getting too hot in the day, and certainly enough to give privacy at night.

After hand washing, I hung them up to dry and they finished off drying up on the curtain rod. There are still creases in the fabric from being folded in packaging, so this is one that needs to be steam straightened.

There is no bad or weird smell to the fabric. There is no satin-y shine to the fabric (the gold print is shiny though, of course).

Overall an unexpectedly good purchase. I would buy from this brand again.
